# Commit messages (Conventional Commits)

Follow [docs/COMMITS.md](../../docs/COMMITS.md) and [Conventional Commits 1.0.0](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).

```
<type>[optional scope][optional !]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## Types

`feat` (MINOR), `fix` (PATCH), `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`.

## Scopes (this repo)

`core`, `cli`, `web`, `tui`, `web-ui`, `ci`, `docker`, `release`, `packaging`, `docs`, `skills`, `deps` — omit when cross-cutting.

## Rules

- Imperative subject, lowercase start, no trailing period, ~72 chars.
- Breaking: `type(scope)!:` and/or `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer → MAJOR.
- One logical change per commit; body explains *why* when non-obvious.
- Never include secrets or real production identifiers in messages.
- Root `npm install` enables Husky **commitlint** on `git commit`; CI job **`commitlint`** enforces on PR/push.

## Examples

```
fix(cli): resolve clippy redundant_closure in doctor_init
ci: replace gitleaks-action with CLI install
feat(web-ui)!: migrate to Tailwind CSS v4

BREAKING CHANGE: postcss now requires @tailwindcss/postcss.
```

Use HEREDOC for multi-line commits: `git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF' ... EOF)"`.
